   <topic>DISKSPACE Function</topic>
    <description>DISKSPACE() returns the number of unused bytes on the disk where the current table is stored.
 </description>
   
   <prototype>Bytes_Available as N = DISKSPACE()</prototype>

   <example><![CDATA[diskspace() -> 22028238.000000, if there are 22,028,238 bytes free on the disk.]]></example>
   
